title: 820-4924-A Not turning on 2015
message:
Liquid Damage Macbook retina 2015

green light no power 


ultrasonic cleaned and made sure it was dry 

plugged it in and while measuring smoke came out of the board

q7560 had a hole in it 

replaced it with 2013 board (slightly different part number) 

anyways same thing just the light nothing

pp3v3_s5 is not constant on L7560


ppbus_G3H is 12.57

title: 820-4924-A Not turning on 2015
message: Q7560 was obviously dead and U7501 is dead too likely. There is also a good chance the 3v3 bus went high due to the shorted FET. What is resistance to GND on L7560? Replace U7501 if resistance looks ok.

title: 820-4924-A Not turning on 2015
message:
ok so i injected voltage to that pin and other connected components. nothing getting hot 

removed l7520 and short gone. i thought it was the coil. i was obviously wrong 
p5vs3_vsw had the short rail 

removed q7520 and short gone 

now replaced that, and u7501 

now getting 3.3v constant and cpu getting 1.7v 

but nothing on display with brand new battery plugged in 

feel so close but yet so far

title: 820-4924-A Not turning on 2015
message: Yeah, my bet is on that 3V3 went high and killed stuff on that rail. Does a USB mouse light up when plugged in?

title: 820-4924-A Not turning on 2015
message: Bleh :(. Give the board a good inspection for corrosion, but I suspect 3V went high. There is so much stuff on the 3V rail that it is not practical to fix this.
